root: ^[Larry the Fisherman] Aye, ye remember the time ye tried fishing when you were just a youngin’? Ye thought ye had to go to the fish, not the fish coming to ye! Argharghargh!
^[Larry the Fisherman] Ye didn’t let go when th’ pole started wrangling, and it went “plop!” in the ocean.
^[Larry the Fisherman] Yer mom and th’ neighbors sure were angry at me fer not helping ye.
^[Larry the Fisherman] Ye start learning young, heh. Good times.
